<glossary><definition id="fs-idp58635552"><term>dynamics</term><meaning id="fs-idp72961424">the study of how forces affect the motion of objects and systems</meaning></definition><definition id="fs-idp72838384"><term>external force</term><meaning id="fs-idp18928624">a force acting on an object or system that originates outside of the object or system</meaning></definition><definition id="fs-idp70052112"><term>force</term><meaning id="fs-idp45464192">a push or pull on an object with a specific magnitude and direction; can be represented by vectors; can be expressed as a multiple of a standard force</meaning></definition><definition id="fs-idp11321744"><term>free-body diagram</term><meaning id="fs-idp72312848">a diagram showing all external forces acting on a body</meaning></definition><definition id="fs-idp30189824"><term>net external force</term><meaning id="fs-idp68308160">the sum of all external forces acting on an object or <emphasis effect="italics">system</emphasis></meaning></definition><definition id="fs-idp42033536"><term>net force</term><meaning id="fs-idp12657072">the sum of all forces acting on an object or system</meaning></definition></glossary>


